{
  "texts": [
    "Effect of identifying different numbers of nonsensical conceptsFigure 4 illustrates the effect of identifying different numbers of nonsensical concepts on the performance of the Llama 2 model in generating commonsense explanations, with Fig. 4a displaying the results on the ComVE dataset and Fig.",
    "4b showing the results on the CSE dataset.",
    "After identifying these nonsensical concepts, implicit knowledge is generated based on them, which is then used to create knowledge-augmented prompts.",
    "In Fig. 4, the different color lines in the charts represent various sizes of the Llama 2 model as the explanation generator, and the title of each chart refers to the knowledge generator.",
    "The x-axis represents the number of nonsensical concepts, while the y-axis shows the corresponding BERTScore and BLEU performance."
  ]
}